{"source": "docs", "batch_index": 153, "chunks": [{"chunk_id": "6dfe900e6f22", "text": "Both get you fed, but they work differently! By the end of this guide, you'll understand both approaches.", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "Why Jac?", "chunk_id": "6dfe900e6f22"}}, {"chunk_id": "c42c3f1c6566", "text": "---", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "Why Jac?", "chunk_id": "c42c3f1c6566"}}, {"chunk_id": "483530c24cad", "text": "## 2. Setting Up: Your First Program\n\nEvery Jac program needs a place to start. We use a special block called `with entry`:", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "2. Setting Up: Your First Program", "chunk_id": "483530c24cad"}}, {"chunk_id": "48846d4b2a0d", "text": "<div class=\"code-block\">", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "2. Setting Up: Your First Program", "chunk_id": "48846d4b2a0d"}}, {"chunk_id": "70af2c6b09fb", "text": "```jac\nwith entry {\n    print(\"Hello, World!\");\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "2. Setting Up: Your First Program", "chunk_id": "70af2c6b09fb"}}, {"chunk_id": "e5a8c8412f8a", "text": "</div>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "2. Setting Up: Your First Program", "chunk_id": "e5a8c8412f8a"}}, {"chunk_id": "1a2ee1249277", "text": "**What's happening here?**", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "2. Setting Up: Your First Program", "chunk_id": "1a2ee1249277"}}, {"chunk_id": "f8c13f669813", "text": "- `with entry` - This is where your program starts\n- `print()` - This is a **function** that displays text on the screen\n- `\"Hello, World!\"` - This is text (called a **string**)\n- `;` - Every instruction ends with a semicolon\n- `{}` - Curly braces group instructions together", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "2. Setting Up: Your First Program", "chunk_id": "f8c13f669813"}}, {"chunk_id": "89dc2cf037bb", "text": "**Try it yourself:** Change \"Hello, World!\" to your name!", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "2. Setting Up: Your First Program", "chunk_id": "89dc2cf037bb"}}, {"chunk_id": "48846d4b2a0d", "text": "<div class=\"code-block\">", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "2. Setting Up: Your First Program", "chunk_id": "48846d4b2a0d"}}, {"chunk_id": "a147fe953a92", "text": "```jac\nwith entry {\n    print(\"Hello, my name is Alice!\");\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "2. Setting Up: Your First Program", "chunk_id": "a147fe953a92"}}, {"chunk_id": "e5a8c8412f8a", "text": "</div>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "2. Setting Up: Your First Program", "chunk_id": "e5a8c8412f8a"}}, {"chunk_id": "a7f803659024", "text": "---", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "2. Setting Up: Your First Program", "chunk_id": "a7f803659024"}}, {"chunk_id": "24cb5ecf2bfd", "text": "## 3. The Basics: Variables and Data", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "3. The Basics: Variables and Data", "chunk_id": "24cb5ecf2bfd"}}, {"chunk_id": "ae47a3ee880e", "text": "### 3.1 What is a Variable?\n\nA variable is like a labeled box where you store information. You give it a name, and you can put different things in it.", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "3.1 What is a Variable?", "chunk_id": "ae47a3ee880e"}}, {"chunk_id": "dd3257d4857c", "text": "<div class=\"code-block\">", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "3.1 What is a Variable?", "chunk_id": "dd3257d4857c"}}, {"chunk_id": "5cbbc5cadf3d", "text": "```jac\nwith entry {\n    # Create a variable\n    name = \"Alice\";\n    age = 25;\n    height = 5.6;\n\n    print(name);    # Shows: Alice\n    print(age);     # Shows: 25\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "3.1 What is a Variable?", "chunk_id": "5cbbc5cadf3d"}}, {"chunk_id": "5b508f1f69d4", "text": "</div>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "3.1 What is a Variable?", "chunk_id": "5b508f1f69d4"}}, {"chunk_id": "222e68c1d5d2", "text": "**Lines starting with `#` are comments** - they're notes for humans, the computer ignores them.", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "3.1 What is a Variable?", "chunk_id": "222e68c1d5d2"}}, {"chunk_id": "d84bb954de80", "text": "### 3.2 Types of Data\n\nJust like in real life, data comes in different types:", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "3.2 Types of Data", "chunk_id": "d84bb954de80"}}, {"chunk_id": "c282886c9403", "text": "#### Text (Strings)\n\n<div class=\"code-block\">", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "Text (Strings)", "chunk_id": "c282886c9403"}}, {"chunk_id": "842f77f2f9cf", "text": "```jac\nwith entry {\n    greeting = \"Hello\";\n    name = \"Bob\";\n    message = \"Welcome to Jac!\";\n\n    print(greeting);  # Shows: Hello\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "Text (Strings)", "chunk_id": "842f77f2f9cf"}}, {"chunk_id": "64dbe220e099", "text": "</div>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "Text (Strings)", "chunk_id": "64dbe220e099"}}, {"chunk_id": "42279cc1a5b1", "text": "Strings go inside quotes: `\"like this\"` or `'like this'`", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "Text (Strings)", "chunk_id": "42279cc1a5b1"}}, {"chunk_id": "6ed5168a3d56", "text": "#### Numbers (Integers)\n\n<div class=\"code-block\">", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "Numbers (Integers)", "chunk_id": "6ed5168a3d56"}}, {"chunk_id": "42dfe177927c", "text": "```jac\nwith entry {\n    apples = 5;\n    students = 30;\n    year = 2024;\n\n    print(apples);  # Shows: 5\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "Numbers (Integers)", "chunk_id": "42dfe177927c"}}, {"chunk_id": "062f27905248", "text": "</div>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "Numbers (Integers)", "chunk_id": "062f27905248"}}, {"chunk_id": "ebaab15da06e", "text": "Whole numbers with no decimal point.", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "Numbers (Integers)", "chunk_id": "ebaab15da06e"}}, {"chunk_id": "efc3901b42c8", "text": "#### Numbers (Floats)\n\n<div class=\"code-block\">", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "Numbers (Floats)", "chunk_id": "efc3901b42c8"}}, {"chunk_id": "c5513741c774", "text": "```jac\nwith entry {\n    temperature = 72.5;\n    price = 19.99;\n    pi = 3.14159;\n\n    print(temperature);  # Shows: 72.5\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "Numbers (Floats)", "chunk_id": "c5513741c774"}}, {"chunk_id": "43abe16ad2d0", "text": "</div>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "Numbers (Floats)", "chunk_id": "43abe16ad2d0"}}, {"chunk_id": "30e79ba9422c", "text": "Numbers with decimal points.", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "Numbers (Floats)", "chunk_id": "30e79ba9422c"}}, {"chunk_id": "0383c07d1523", "text": "#### True or False (Booleans)\n\n<div class=\"code-block\">", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "True or False (Booleans)", "chunk_id": "0383c07d1523"}}, {"chunk_id": "2e1aca38dcdf", "text": "```jac\nwith entry {\n    is_raining = True;\n    is_sunny = False;\n\n    print(is_raining);  # Shows: True\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "True or False (Booleans)", "chunk_id": "2e1aca38dcdf"}}, {"chunk_id": "baf6c742ecf9", "text": "</div>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "True or False (Booleans)", "chunk_id": "baf6c742ecf9"}}, {"chunk_id": "890e31bad8fa", "text": "Only two values: `True` or `False` (notice the capital letters!)", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "True or False (Booleans)", "chunk_id": "890e31bad8fa"}}, {"chunk_id": "d9586ab9abf9", "text": "### 3.3 Type Annotations (Recommended!)\n\nYou can tell Jac what type of data a variable should hold:", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "3.3 Type Annotations (Recommended!)", "chunk_id": "d9586ab9abf9"}}, {"chunk_id": "e0167febd73e", "text": "<div class=\"code-block\">", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "3.3 Type Annotations (Recommended!)", "chunk_id": "e0167febd73e"}}, {"chunk_id": "9e665b4d47fd", "text": "```jac\nwith entry {\n    name: str = \"Alice\";      # str means string (text)\n    age: int = 25;            # int means integer (whole number)\n    height: float = 5.6;      # float means decimal number\n    is_student: bool = True;  # bool means boolean (True/False)\n\n    print(f\"{name} is {age} years old\");\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "3.3 Type Annotations (Recommended!)", "chunk_id": "9e665b4d47fd"}}, {"chunk_id": "e0e4a50f60ea", "text": "</div>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "3.3 Type Annotations (Recommended!)", "chunk_id": "e0e4a50f60ea"}}, {"chunk_id": "35345efdb069", "text": "**Pro tip:** The `f` before a string lets you insert variables using `{variable_name}`", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "3.3 Type Annotations (Recommended!)", "chunk_id": "35345efdb069"}}, {"chunk_id": "453388df2238", "text": "### 3.4 Doing Math\n\nYou can calculate with numbers:", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "3.4 Doing Math", "chunk_id": "453388df2238"}}, {"chunk_id": "affb04a61948", "text": "<div class=\"code-block\">", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "3.4 Doing Math", "chunk_id": "affb04a61948"}}, {"chunk_id": "309307ac0d7e", "text": "```jac\nwith entry {\n    # Basic math\n    sum = 5 + 3;        # Addition: 8\n    difference = 10 - 4; # Subtraction: 6\n    product = 6 * 7;     # Multiplication: 42\n    quotient = 20 / 4;   # Division: 5.0\n\n    print(sum);         # Shows: 8\n    print(product);     # Shows: 42\n\n    # More operations\n    remainder = 17 % 5;  # Modulo (remainder): 2\n    power = 2 ** 3;      # Exponent: 8 (2³)\n\n    # Combined operations\n    total = (5 + 3) * 2;  # Use parentheses like in math: 16\n\n    print(total);\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "3.4 Doing Math", "chunk_id": "309307ac0d7e"}}, {"chunk_id": "dfaec72c22fa", "text": "</div>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "3.4 Doing Math", "chunk_id": "dfaec72c22fa"}}, {"chunk_id": "e2dca629846a", "text": "### 3.5 Changing Variables\n\nVariables can change their value:", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "3.5 Changing Variables", "chunk_id": "e2dca629846a"}}, {"chunk_id": "497813fb9a49", "text": "<div class=\"code-block\">", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "3.5 Changing Variables", "chunk_id": "497813fb9a49"}}, {"chunk_id": "5554fef16430", "text": "```jac\nwith entry {\n    score = 0;\n    print(score);    # Shows: 0\n\n    score = 10;\n    print(score);    # Shows: 10\n\n    score = score + 5;  # Add 5 to current value\n    print(score);    # Shows: 15\n\n    # Shortcut for score = score + 5\n    score += 5;\n    print(score);    # Shows: 20\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "3.5 Changing Variables", "chunk_id": "5554fef16430"}}, {"chunk_id": "a622791e07fd", "text": "</div>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "3.5 Changing Variables", "chunk_id": "a622791e07fd"}}, {"chunk_id": "2473245bf8ef", "text": "**Common shortcuts:**", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "3.5 Changing Variables", "chunk_id": "2473245bf8ef"}}], "near_dup_candidates": []}